The Magic Fountain
4.5
#10 of 1,516 things to do in Barcelona
Points of Interest & LandmarksFountains
Write a review
About
A combination display of water, music and light which was originally built in 1929. It was restored in 1992 and provides a spectacular show every half hour.
Duration: 1-2 hours

At the foot of Montjuic is a grand palace with mighty pillars and the Magic Fountain. Unfortunately when I visited there was nothing magical about the fountain. It had no water in and was not working.

The whole area was cordoned off and there seemed to be cameras and lighting about so I am not sure if they were using the area for filming. There were security staff dotted about stopping people from entering.

Maybe I just turned up on the wrong day?

A great free place to kill a few hours
Jul 2024 • Family
The fountain (and all others in Barcelona) haven’t been running for the last two years because of the drought, but if it is running, it’s a great place to hang out. There are drinks and snacks available in the area for purchase, you can bring a chair or just sit in the grass, and enjoy. A great place to bring the kids for a little enjoyment.
